{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Today I want to talk about design,"},{"time":2000,"text":"but not design as we usually think about it."},{"time":5000,"text":"I want to talk about what is happening now"},{"time":7000,"text":"in our scientific, biotechnological culture,"},{"time":10000,"text":"where, for really the first time in history,"},{"time":13000,"text":"we have the power to design bodies,"},{"time":15000,"text":"to design animal bodies,"},{"time":17000,"text":"to design human bodies."},{"time":20000,"text":"In the history of our planet,"},{"time":24000,"text":"there have been three great waves of evolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27000,"text":"The first wave of evolution"},{"time":29000,"text":"is what we think of as Darwinian evolution."},{"time":32000,"text":"So, as you all know,"},{"time":34000,"text":"species lived in particular ecological niches"},{"time":36000,"text":"and particular environments,"},{"time":38000,"text":"and the pressures of those environments"},{"time":40000,"text":"selected which changes,"},{"time":42000,"text":"through random mutation in species,"},{"time":44000,"text":"were going to be preserved."},{"time":46000,"text":"Then human beings stepped out"},{"time":49000,"text":"of the Darwinian flow of evolutionary history"},{"time":52000,"text":"and created the second great wave of evolution,"},{"time":56000,"text":"which was we changed the environment"},{"time":59000,"text":"in which we evolved."},{"time":61000,"text":"We altered our ecological niche"},{"time":64000,"text":"by creating civilization."},{"time":66000,"text":"And that has been the second great --"},{"time":68000,"text":"couple 100,000 years, 150,000 years --"},{"time":71000,"text":"flow of our evolution."},{"time":73000,"text":"By changing our environment,"},{"time":75000,"text":"we put new pressures"},{"time":77000,"text":"on our bodies to evolve."},{"time":79000,"text":"Whether it was through settling down in agricultural communities,"},{"time":82000,"text":"all the way through modern medicine,"},{"time":85000,"text":"we have changed our own evolution."},{"time":88000,"text":"Now we're entering a third great wave"},{"time":91000,"text":"of evolutionary history,"},{"time":93000,"text":"which has been called many things:"},{"time":95000,"text":"\"intentional evolution,\""},{"time":97000,"text":"\"evolution by design\" --"},{"time":99000,"text":"very different than intelligent design --"},{"time":101000,"text":"whereby we are actually now"},{"time":104000,"text":"intentionally designing and altering"},{"time":108000,"text":"the physiological forms that inhabit our planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111000,"text":"So I want to take you through a kind of whirlwind tour of that"},{"time":114000,"text":"and then at the end talk a little bit"},{"time":116000,"text":"about what some of the implications are for us"},{"time":119000,"text":"and for our species, as well as our cultures,"},{"time":122000,"text":"because of this change."},{"time":124000,"text":"Now we actually have been doing it for a long time."},{"time":129000,"text":"We started selectively breeding animals"},{"time":132000,"text":"many, many thousands of years ago."},{"time":135000,"text":"And if you think of dogs for example,"},{"time":137000,"text":"dogs are now intentionally-designed creatures."},{"time":141000,"text":"There isn't a dog on this earth that's a natural creature."},{"time":144000,"text":"Dogs are the result"},{"time":146000,"text":"of selectively breeding traits that we like."},{"time":149000,"text":"But we had to do it the hard way in the old days"},{"time":152000,"text":"by choosing offspring that looked a particular way"},{"time":154000,"text":"and then breeding them."},{"time":156000,"text":"We don't have to do it that way anymore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":158000,"text":"This is a beefalo."},{"time":161000,"text":"A beefalo is a buffalo-cattle hybrid."},{"time":165000,"text":"And they are now making them,"},{"time":167000,"text":"and someday, perhaps pretty soon,"},{"time":169000,"text":"you will have beefalo patties"},{"time":171000,"text":"in your local supermarket."},{"time":174000,"text":"This is a geep,"},{"time":176000,"text":"a goat-sheep hybrid."},{"time":179000,"text":"The scientists that made this cute little creature"},{"time":182000,"text":"ended up slaughtering it and eating it afterwards."},{"time":185000,"text":"I think they said it tasted like chicken."},{"time":188000,"text":"This is a cama."},{"time":190000,"text":"A cama is a camel-llama hybrid,"},{"time":194000,"text":"created to try to get the hardiness of a camel"},{"time":197000,"text":"with some of the personality traits"},{"time":199000,"text":"of a llama."},{"time":201000,"text":"And they are now using these in certain cultures."},{"time":205000,"text":"Then there's the liger."},{"time":207000,"text":"This is the largest cat in the world --"},{"time":210000,"text":"the lion-tiger hybrid."},{"time":212000,"text":"It's bigger than a tiger."},{"time":214000,"text":"And in the case of the liger,"},{"time":216000,"text":"there actually have been one or two that have been seen in the wild."},{"time":219000,"text":"But these were created by scientists"},{"time":222000,"text":"using both selective breeding and genetic technology."},{"time":225000,"text":"And then finally, everybody's favorite,"},{"time":228000,"text":"the zorse."},{"time":230000,"text":"None of this is Photoshopped. These are real creatures."},{"time":233000,"text":"And so one of the things we've been doing"},{"time":235000,"text":"is using genetic enhancement,"},{"time":238000,"text":"or genetic manipulation,"},{"time":240000,"text":"of normal selective breeding"},{"time":243000,"text":"pushed a little bit through genetics."},{"time":245000,"text":"And if that were all this was about,"},{"time":248000,"text":"then it would be an interesting thing."},{"time":250000,"text":"But something much, much more powerful"},{"time":253000,"text":"is happening now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256000,"text":"These are normal mammalian cells"},{"time":259000,"text":"genetically engineered with a bioluminescent gene"},{"time":262000,"text":"taken out of deep-sea jellyfish."},{"time":264000,"text":"We all know that some deep-sea creatures glow."},{"time":268000,"text":"Well, they've now taken that gene, that bioluminescent gene,"},{"time":271000,"text":"and put it into mammal cells."},{"time":273000,"text":"These are normal cells."},{"time":275000,"text":"And what you see here"},{"time":277000,"text":"is these cells glowing in the dark"},{"time":279000,"text":"under certain wavelengths of light."},{"time":282000,"text":"Once they could do that with cells, they could do it with organisms."},{"time":285000,"text":"So they did it with mouse pups,"},{"time":289000,"text":"kittens."},{"time":291000,"text":"And by the way, the reason the kittens here are orange and these are green"},{"time":295000,"text":"is because that's a bioluminescent gene from coral,"},{"time":298000,"text":"while this is from jellyfish."},{"time":301000,"text":"They did it with pigs."},{"time":304000,"text":"They did it with puppies."},{"time":306000,"text":"And, in fact,"},{"time":308000,"text":"they did it with monkeys."},{"time":310000,"text":"And if you can do it with monkeys --"},{"time":312000,"text":"though the great leap in trying to genetically manipulate"},{"time":315000,"text":"is actually between monkeys and apes --"},{"time":317000,"text":"if they can do it in monkeys,"},{"time":319000,"text":"they can probably figure out how to do it in apes,"},{"time":321000,"text":"which means they can do it in human beings."},{"time":325000,"text":"In other words, it is theoretically possible"},{"time":328000,"text":"that before too long we will be biotechnologically capable"},{"time":331000,"text":"of creating human beings"},{"time":334000,"text":"that glow in the dark."},{"time":339000,"text":"Be easier to find us at night."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341000,"text":"And in fact, right now in many states,"},{"time":344000,"text":"you can go out and you can buy bioluminescent pets."},{"time":347000,"text":"These are zebra fish. They're normally black and silver."},{"time":350000,"text":"These are zebra fish that have been genetically engineered"},{"time":353000,"text":"to be yellow, green, red,"},{"time":355000,"text":"and they are actually available now in certain states."},{"time":358000,"text":"Other states have banned them."},{"time":360000,"text":"Nobody knows what to do with these kinds of creatures."},{"time":363000,"text":"There is no area of the government -- not the EPA or the FDA --"},{"time":366000,"text":"that controls genetically-engineered pets."},{"time":370000,"text":"And so some states have decided to allow them,"},{"time":373000,"text":"some states have decided to ban them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377000,"text":"Some of you may have read"},{"time":379000,"text":"about the FDA's consideration right now"},{"time":381000,"text":"of genetically-engineered salmon."},{"time":384000,"text":"The salmon on top"},{"time":386000,"text":"is a genetically engineered Chinook salmon,"},{"time":388000,"text":"using a gene from these salmon"},{"time":390000,"text":"and from one other fish that we eat,"},{"time":392000,"text":"to make it grow much faster"},{"time":394000,"text":"using a lot less feed."},{"time":396000,"text":"And right now the FDA is trying to make a final decision"},{"time":399000,"text":"on whether, pretty soon, you could be eating this fish --"},{"time":402000,"text":"it'll be sold in the stores."},{"time":404000,"text":"And before you get too worried about it,"},{"time":406000,"text":"here in the United States,"},{"time":408000,"text":"the majority of food you buy in the supermarket"},{"time":410000,"text":"already has genetically-modified components to it."},{"time":414000,"text":"So even as we worry about it,"},{"time":416000,"text":"we have allowed it to go on in this country -- much different in Europe --"},{"time":419000,"text":"without any regulation,"},{"time":421000,"text":"and even without any identification on the package."}]},{"cues":[{"time":425000,"text":"These are all the first cloned animals"},{"time":428000,"text":"of their type."},{"time":430000,"text":"So in the lower right here,"},{"time":432000,"text":"you have Dolly, the first cloned sheep --"},{"time":434000,"text":"now happily stuffed in a museum in Edinburgh;"},{"time":437000,"text":"Ralph the rat, the first cloned rat;"},{"time":440000,"text":"CC the cat, for cloned cat;"},{"time":443000,"text":"Snuppy, the first cloned dog --"},{"time":445000,"text":"Snuppy for Seoul National University puppy --"},{"time":448000,"text":"created in South Korea"},{"time":450000,"text":"by the very same man that some of you may remember"},{"time":452000,"text":"had to end up resigning in disgrace"},{"time":454000,"text":"because he claimed he had cloned a human embryo, which he had not."},{"time":458000,"text":"He actually was the first person"},{"time":460000,"text":"to clone a dog, which is a very difficult thing to do,"},{"time":463000,"text":"because dog genomes are very plastic."},{"time":466000,"text":"This is Prometea, the first cloned horse."},{"time":469000,"text":"It's a Haflinger horse cloned in Italy,"},{"time":471000,"text":"a real \"gold ring\" of cloning,"},{"time":473000,"text":"because there are many horses that win important races"},{"time":476000,"text":"who are geldings."},{"time":478000,"text":"In other words, the equipment to put them out to stud"},{"time":481000,"text":"has been removed."},{"time":483000,"text":"But if you can clone that horse,"},{"time":485000,"text":"you can have both the advantage of having a gelding run in the race"},{"time":488000,"text":"and his identical genetic duplicate"},{"time":491000,"text":"can then be put out to stud."},{"time":494000,"text":"These were the first cloned calves,"},{"time":496000,"text":"the first cloned grey wolves,"},{"time":498000,"text":"and then, finally,"},{"time":500000,"text":"the first cloned piglets:"},{"time":502000,"text":"Alexis, Chista, Carrel, Janie and Dotcom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":510000,"text":"In addition, we've started to use cloning technology"},{"time":513000,"text":"to try to save endangered species."},{"time":516000,"text":"This is the use of animals now"},{"time":518000,"text":"to create drugs and other things in their bodies"},{"time":521000,"text":"that we want to create."},{"time":523000,"text":"So with antithrombin in that goat --"},{"time":525000,"text":"that goat has been genetically modified"},{"time":527000,"text":"so that the molecules of its milk"},{"time":530000,"text":"actually include the molecule of antithrombin"},{"time":533000,"text":"that GTC Genetics wants to create."},{"time":536000,"text":"And then in addition, transgenic pigs, knockout pigs,"},{"time":539000,"text":"from the National Institute of Animal Science in South Korea,"},{"time":543000,"text":"are pigs that they are going to use, in fact,"},{"time":546000,"text":"to try to create all kinds of drugs"},{"time":550000,"text":"and other industrial types of chemicals"},{"time":554000,"text":"that they want the blood and the milk"},{"time":556000,"text":"of these animals"},{"time":558000,"text":"to produce for them,"},{"time":560000,"text":"instead of producing them in an industrial way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564000,"text":"These are two creatures"},{"time":566000,"text":"that were created"},{"time":569000,"text":"in order to save endangered species."},{"time":571000,"text":"The guar"},{"time":573000,"text":"is an endangered Southeast Asian ungulate."},{"time":577000,"text":"A somatic cell, a body cell,"},{"time":579000,"text":"was taken from its body,"},{"time":581000,"text":"gestated in the ovum of a cow,"},{"time":583000,"text":"and then that cow gave birth to a guar."},{"time":587000,"text":"Same thing happened with the mouflon,"},{"time":589000,"text":"where it's an endangered species of sheep."},{"time":592000,"text":"It was gestated in a regular sheep body,"},{"time":598000,"text":"which actually raises an interesting biological problem."},{"time":601000,"text":"We have two kinds of DNA in our bodies."},{"time":603000,"text":"We have our nucleic DNA"},{"time":605000,"text":"that everybody thinks of as our DNA,"},{"time":607000,"text":"but we also have DNA in our mitochondria,"},{"time":609000,"text":"which are the energy packets of the cell."},{"time":612000,"text":"That DNA is passed down through our mothers."},{"time":615000,"text":"So really, what you end up having here"},{"time":618000,"text":"is not a guar and not a mouflon,"},{"time":620000,"text":"but a guar"},{"time":622000,"text":"with cow mitochondria,"},{"time":624000,"text":"and therefore cow mitochondrial DNA,"},{"time":626000,"text":"and a mouflon with another species of sheep's"},{"time":629000,"text":"mitochondrial DNA."},{"time":631000,"text":"These are really hybrids, not pure animals."},{"time":634000,"text":"And it raises the question of how we're going to define animal species"},{"time":637000,"text":"in the age of biotechnology --"},{"time":639000,"text":"a question that we're not really sure yet"},{"time":642000,"text":"how to solve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644000,"text":"This lovely creature"},{"time":646000,"text":"is an Asian cockroach."},{"time":649000,"text":"And what they've done here"},{"time":651000,"text":"is they've put electrodes in its ganglia and its brain"},{"time":655000,"text":"and then a transmitter on top,"},{"time":657000,"text":"and it's on a big computer tracking ball."},{"time":659000,"text":"And now, using a joystick,"},{"time":661000,"text":"they can send this creature"},{"time":663000,"text":"around the lab"},{"time":665000,"text":"and control whether it goes left or right,"},{"time":667000,"text":"forwards or backwards."},{"time":669000,"text":"They've created a kind of insect bot,"},{"time":671000,"text":"or bugbot."},{"time":673000,"text":"It gets worse than that -- or perhaps better than that."},{"time":676000,"text":"This actually is one of DARPA's very important --"},{"time":679000,"text":"DARPA is the Defense Research Agency --"},{"time":681000,"text":"one of their projects."},{"time":683000,"text":"These goliath beetles"},{"time":685000,"text":"are wired in their wings."},{"time":687000,"text":"They have a computer chip strapped to their backs,"},{"time":689000,"text":"and they can fly these creatures around the lab."},{"time":693000,"text":"They can make them go left, right. They can make them take off."},{"time":695000,"text":"They can't actually make them land."},{"time":697000,"text":"They put them about one inch above the ground,"},{"time":699000,"text":"and then they shut everything off and they go pfft."},{"time":701000,"text":"But it's the closest they can get to a landing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705000,"text":"And in fact, this technology has gotten so developed"},{"time":708000,"text":"that this creature --"},{"time":710000,"text":"this is a moth --"},{"time":712000,"text":"this is the moth in its pupa stage,"},{"time":714000,"text":"and that's when they put the wires in"},{"time":716000,"text":"and they put in the computer technology,"},{"time":719000,"text":"so that when the moth actually emerges as a moth,"},{"time":722000,"text":"it is already prewired."},{"time":725000,"text":"The wires are already in its body,"},{"time":728000,"text":"and they can just hook it up to their technology,"},{"time":731000,"text":"and now they've got these bugbots"},{"time":733000,"text":"that they can send out for surveillance."},{"time":735000,"text":"They can put little cameras on them"},{"time":737000,"text":"and perhaps someday deliver"},{"time":739000,"text":"other kinds of ordinance"},{"time":741000,"text":"to warzones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744000,"text":"It's not just insects."},{"time":746000,"text":"This is the ratbot, or the robo-rat"},{"time":748000,"text":"by Sanjiv Talwar at SUNY Downstate."},{"time":751000,"text":"Again, it's got technology --"},{"time":753000,"text":"it's got electrodes going into its left and right hemispheres;"},{"time":756000,"text":"it's got a camera on top of its head."},{"time":759000,"text":"The scientists can make this creature"},{"time":761000,"text":"go left, right."},{"time":763000,"text":"They have it running through mazes, controlling where it's going."},{"time":766000,"text":"They've now created an organic robot."},{"time":770000,"text":"The graduate students"},{"time":772000,"text":"in Sanjiv Talwar's lab"},{"time":774000,"text":"said, \"Is this ethical?"},{"time":776000,"text":"We've taken away the autonomy of this animal.\""},{"time":779000,"text":"I'll get back to that in a minute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":781000,"text":"There's also been work done with monkeys."},{"time":784000,"text":"This is Miguel Nicolelis of Duke."},{"time":787000,"text":"He took owl monkeys,"},{"time":789000,"text":"wired them up"},{"time":791000,"text":"so that a computer watched their brains while they moved,"},{"time":793000,"text":"especially looking at the movement of their right arm."},{"time":795000,"text":"The computer learned what the monkey brain did"},{"time":797000,"text":"to move its arm in various ways."},{"time":799000,"text":"They then hooked it up to a prosthetic arm,"},{"time":802000,"text":"which you see here in the picture,"},{"time":804000,"text":"put the arm in another room."},{"time":806000,"text":"Pretty soon, the computer learned, by reading the monkey's brainwaves,"},{"time":809000,"text":"to make that arm in the other room"},{"time":811000,"text":"do whatever the monkey's arm did."},{"time":814000,"text":"Then he put a video monitor"},{"time":816000,"text":"in the monkey's cage"},{"time":818000,"text":"that showed the monkey this prosthetic arm,"},{"time":820000,"text":"and the monkey got fascinated."},{"time":822000,"text":"The monkey recognized that whatever she did with her arm,"},{"time":824000,"text":"this prosthetic arm would do."},{"time":826000,"text":"And eventually she was moving it and moving it,"},{"time":829000,"text":"and eventually stopped moving her right arm"},{"time":831000,"text":"and, staring at the screen,"},{"time":833000,"text":"could move the prosthetic arm in the other room"},{"time":836000,"text":"only with her brainwaves --"},{"time":838000,"text":"which means that monkey"},{"time":840000,"text":"became the first primate in the history of the world"},{"time":843000,"text":"to have three independent functional arms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":847000,"text":"And it's not just technology"},{"time":849000,"text":"that we're putting into animals."},{"time":851000,"text":"This is Thomas DeMarse at the University of Florida."},{"time":854000,"text":"He took 20,000 and then 60,000"},{"time":856000,"text":"disaggregated rat neurons --"},{"time":859000,"text":"so these are just individual neurons from rats --"},{"time":862000,"text":"put them on a chip."},{"time":864000,"text":"They self-aggregated into a network,"},{"time":867000,"text":"became an integrated chip."},{"time":870000,"text":"And he used that"},{"time":872000,"text":"as the IT piece"},{"time":874000,"text":"of a mechanism which ran a flight simulator."},{"time":877000,"text":"So now we have organic computer chips"},{"time":880000,"text":"made out of living, self-aggregating neurons."},{"time":885000,"text":"Finally, Mussa-Ivaldi of Northwestern"},{"time":888000,"text":"took a completely intact,"},{"time":890000,"text":"independent lamprey eel brain."},{"time":893000,"text":"This is a brain from a lamprey eel."},{"time":895000,"text":"It is living --"},{"time":897000,"text":"fully-intact brain in a nutrient medium"},{"time":900000,"text":"with these electrodes going off to the sides,"},{"time":903000,"text":"attached photosensitive sensors to the brain,"},{"time":906000,"text":"put it into a cart --"},{"time":908000,"text":"here's the cart, the brain is sitting there in the middle --"},{"time":911000,"text":"and using this brain as the sole processor for this cart,"},{"time":914000,"text":"when you turn on a light and shine it at the cart,"},{"time":916000,"text":"the cart moves toward the light;"},{"time":918000,"text":"when you turn it off, it moves away."},{"time":920000,"text":"It's photophilic."},{"time":922000,"text":"So now we have a complete"},{"time":925000,"text":"living lamprey eel brain."},{"time":927000,"text":"Is it thinking lamprey eel thoughts,"},{"time":929000,"text":"sitting there in its nutrient medium?"},{"time":931000,"text":"I don't know,"},{"time":933000,"text":"but in fact it is a fully living brain"},{"time":937000,"text":"that we have managed to keep alive"},{"time":940000,"text":"to do our bidding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":943000,"text":"So, we are now at the stage"},{"time":946000,"text":"where we are creating creatures"},{"time":948000,"text":"for our own purposes."},{"time":950000,"text":"This is a mouse created by Charles Vacanti"},{"time":953000,"text":"of the University of Massachusetts."},{"time":956000,"text":"He altered this mouse"},{"time":959000,"text":"so that it was genetically engineered"},{"time":961000,"text":"to have skin that was less immunoreactive to human skin,"},{"time":964000,"text":"put a polymer scaffolding of an ear under it"},{"time":968000,"text":"and created an ear that could then be taken off the mouse"},{"time":971000,"text":"and transplanted onto a human being."},{"time":973000,"text":"Genetic engineering"},{"time":975000,"text":"coupled with polymer physiotechnology"},{"time":977000,"text":"coupled with xenotransplantation."},{"time":979000,"text":"This is where we are in this process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":982000,"text":"Finally, not that long ago,"},{"time":985000,"text":"Craig Venter created the first artificial cell,"},{"time":988000,"text":"where he took a cell, took a DNA synthesizer,"},{"time":990000,"text":"which is a machine,"},{"time":992000,"text":"created an artificial genome,"},{"time":994000,"text":"put it in a different cell --"},{"time":997000,"text":"the genome was not of the cell he put it in --"},{"time":1000000,"text":"and that cell then reproduced"},{"time":1002000,"text":"as the other cell."},{"time":1004000,"text":"In other words,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"that was the first creature in the history of the world"},{"time":1008000,"text":"that had a computer as its parent --"},{"time":1010000,"text":"it did not have an organic parent."},{"time":1013000,"text":"And so, asks The Economist:"},{"time":1016000,"text":"\"The first artificial organism and its consequences.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1019000,"text":"So you may have thought"},{"time":1021000,"text":"that the creation of life"},{"time":1023000,"text":"was going to happen in something that looked like that."},{"time":1026000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1028000,"text":"But in fact, that's not what Frankenstein's lab looks like."},{"time":1031000,"text":"This is what Frankenstein's lab looks like."},{"time":1033000,"text":"This is a DNA synthesizer,"},{"time":1035000,"text":"and here at the bottom"},{"time":1037000,"text":"are just bottles of A, T, C and G --"},{"time":1039000,"text":"the four chemicals"},{"time":1041000,"text":"that make up our DNA chain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1043000,"text":"And so, we need to ask ourselves some questions."},{"time":1046000,"text":"For the first time in the history of this planet,"},{"time":1049000,"text":"we are able to directly design organisms."},{"time":1052000,"text":"We can manipulate the plasmas of life"},{"time":1054000,"text":"with unprecedented power,"},{"time":1057000,"text":"and it confers on us a responsibility."},{"time":1059000,"text":"Is everything okay?"},{"time":1061000,"text":"Is it okay to manipulate and create"},{"time":1063000,"text":"whatever creatures we want?"},{"time":1065000,"text":"Do we have free reign"},{"time":1067000,"text":"to design animals?"},{"time":1069000,"text":"Do we get to go someday to Pets 'R' Us"},{"time":1072000,"text":"and say, \"Look, I want a dog."},{"time":1074000,"text":"I'd like it to have the head of a Dachshund,"},{"time":1077000,"text":"the body of a retriever,"},{"time":1079000,"text":"maybe some pink fur,"},{"time":1081000,"text":"and let's make it glow in the dark\"?"},{"time":1083000,"text":"Does industry get to create creatures"},{"time":1085000,"text":"who, in their milk, in their blood, and in their saliva"},{"time":1088000,"text":"and other bodily fluids,"},{"time":1090000,"text":"create the drugs and industrial molecules we want"},{"time":1093000,"text":"and then warehouse them"},{"time":1095000,"text":"as organic manufacturing machines?"},{"time":1098000,"text":"Do we get to create organic robots,"},{"time":1101000,"text":"where we remove the autonomy from these animals"},{"time":1104000,"text":"and turn them just into our playthings?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1107000,"text":"And then the final step of this,"},{"time":1110000,"text":"once we perfect these technologies in animals"},{"time":1112000,"text":"and we start using them in human beings,"},{"time":1114000,"text":"what are the ethical guidelines"},{"time":1116000,"text":"that we will use then?"},{"time":1119000,"text":"It's already happening. It's not science fiction."},{"time":1122000,"text":"We are not only already using these things in animals,"},{"time":1125000,"text":"some of them we're already beginning to use"},{"time":1128000,"text":"on our own bodies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1130000,"text":"We are now taking control of our own evolution."},{"time":1133000,"text":"We are directly designing"},{"time":1135000,"text":"the future of the species of this planet."},{"time":1138000,"text":"It confers upon us an enormous responsibility"},{"time":1141000,"text":"that is not just the responsibility"},{"time":1143000,"text":"of the scientists and the ethicists"},{"time":1145000,"text":"who are thinking about it and writing about it now."},{"time":1147000,"text":"It is the responsibility of everybody"},{"time":1150000,"text":"because it will determine what kind of planet and what kind of bodies"},{"time":1153000,"text":"we will have in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1155000,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1157000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}